MASTER’S PROJECT                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
A Watermarking for Large Language Models 
 
A watermarking framework for large language models (LLMs) that can be embedded with negligible impact on text quality and 
detected using an open-source algorithm. The watermark works by selecting a randomized set of “green” tokens before a word is 
generated, and then promoting their use during sampling. 
SURVEY’S / PUBLICATION                                                                                                                                                                                                      
Website Fingerprinting Attacks and Defense 


Website Fingerprinting Attacks and Defense 
 
Website Fingerprinting (WF) attacks exploit encrypted network traffic to deanonymize users, posing a threat to privacy solutions 
like Tor. Surakav, a defense strategy, utilizes Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) to generate realistic traffic patterns, 
effectively reducing attacker success rates by 57% with minimal overhead, outperforming existing defenses. 
Walking stick with heart attack detection 
 
Featured in the International Journal of Advance, Research, Ideas, and Innovations in Technology (IJARIIT), the prototype 
"Walking Stick with Heart Attack Detection" aims to support senior citizens with heart conditions. This innovative device is 
equipped with a communication channel that promptly alerts medical professionals or emergency services upon detecting a heart 
attack, significantly enhancing the probability of swift medical response by 60%.
